data.description: This 4-bedroom, 2-bath brick ranch home was built in 2016 and you're just minutes away from beautiful beaches, The Zoo, top-rated schools, shopping, dining, and the Woodlawn boat ramp. This home offers ample space for both family living and entertaining with striking curb appeal ,well-maintained landscaping and a welcoming front porch. The open concept floor plan enhances the flow and functionality of the living spaces. The kitchen features granite countertops, lots of cabinets, stainless steel appliances, large corner pantry and a breakfast bar. It's perfect for enjoying casual meals with family and friends. The master suite has a spacious bedroom with boxed ceiling, crown molding and an en-suite bathroom with a large walk-in closet, double vanity, granite countertop, water closet AKA “throne room”, soaking tub, and a separate tile shower. There is a coat closet by the front door - but you will only wear a coat for about a month, linen closets in the guest bath and hall, plantation shutters in the great room and a storm door on the front door to let even more natural light in - as if that is even possible. Step into the backyard to discover peace and quiet. The screened porch and the large, fenced backyard provide a perfect space for outdoor dining, relaxing, or hosting gatherings. The attached two-car garage offers convenience and ample storage space for your vehicles and belongings. This home has been meticulously maintained and is in excellent condition with all hard floors - luxury vinyl plank wood-look flooring, making it move-in ready for the next lucky homeowner. This is a highly sought-after community with a friendly atmosphere and a strong sense of community. There is a playground, park and even basketball hoops on a few cul-de-sacs. The midway area in Gulf Breeze is renowned for its excellent schools, recreational facilities, and proximity to Pensacola and Navarre Beaches on the Gulf of Mexico.
